title.$t: My experience at my CCCD Jamaica Mission Trip

media$title.$t: My experience at my CCCD Jamaica Mission Trip

media$description.$t:
Hey, I went on a deaf mission trip on May 12 to 19th to Knockpatrick Jamaica. It was an amazing experience and I just wanted to share my thoughts about it. Hope you enjoy!

Hi my name is Keefer.
I recently got home last night from Jamaica where I was on a Deaf Mission Trip. It was an amazing experience in Jamaica at CCCD. It's a school in Jamaica where the Deaf go for education. It was a cool experience. On the first day we went to a deaf village and saw a deaf preacher. It was awesome and we all learned a lot. Then we played basketball and soccer and wow the Jamaicans were good at soccer. So then the days that followed we got up in the morning and worked. I made arches and fences using concrete and then cleaned a water tank and just did random jobs. It was cool. Then in the afternoons we played with the kids, mostly soccer, and just talked and hung out. I met a lot of new people. I'm going to try to upload some videos and pictures to show about my week. The people who run CCCD are great people and know what they're doing. I learned a lot of new signs and it was just a kool experience. If you want to give money, please do. That's how they make most of their money. I want to go back, but I don't know if or when I'll get the chance.
